title: For Trade:  Trade- Primers for powder
postcontent:
Well, im in a situation here with a lot of options. Im getting a friend started reloading and the only thing we need is powder. worst case scenario I can lend him a pound of hp38 until this panic dies down. 

Option 1- I have small rifle primers I can spare. Going off powdervalleyinc.com prices(21/k primers, $16/lb powder) I would like to trade 800 tula small rifle primers for a pound of powder best suited for lead cast 45 and/or 38 special. namely winchester 231/hp-38, unique or bullseye. I have been using small rifle primers for 223, 45, 38, 357 and 380 without a problem. they are slightly hotter and have a thicker cup than small pistol primers.

Option 2- My buddy will shortly have an excess of large pistol magnum primers. These can be used in place of large pistol stand primers as long as you knock your load down 10% and work your way back up. They are just a bit hotter. I made him order more than he needed so he has a bartering item. Looking for a powder best suited for 40 and 45acp however will trade these for bullseye or unique, maybe even universal clays and him and I can hash it out.

Throw me your ideas.  In these panickey price gouging times, its tough to get someone started. also- only interested in factory sealed cans.
